<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Diagnostics Manual - Engine Symptoms Diagnostics - Test Procedures - Coolant in Lube Oil
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s305010402.4" svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Coolant in Lube Oil</title>
        <svcprocinfo id="s305010402.4.1">
            <para id="s305010402.4.1.1"></para>
            <table id="t305010403" frame="topbot">
                <title>Causes</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Glow plug sleeve leak</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Injector sleeve leak</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Cylinder head cup plug failure</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Cylinder head gasket leak</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Oil filter base assembly and oil cooler bundle failure</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Front cover gasket damage</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Front cover, cylinder head, or crankcase porosity</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="s305010402.4.2">
            <title>Inspection for Lube Oil Contamination</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check coolant level and oil level gauge to verify oil contamination complaint.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>The presence of coolant in the oil will generally cause the oil to thicken and coagulate
                            giving a gray black chunky appearance.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If coolant in the oil can not be verified, an oil sample can be taken for analysis.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When oil contamination is verified, plug in cylinder block heater, if available, to warm
                    coolant.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove glow plug harnesses, glow plugs, and valve covers. Drain engine oil and remove
                    oil filter.
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Leave oil drain plug out of pan and oil filter cap off.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pressurize cooling system to 96 kPa (14 psi).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If coolant is leaking from oil pan, do the following:</para>
                <figure id="f305010407" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figj08/J08089.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="248px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Cylinder Head Cup Plug Locations</caption>
                </figure>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Inspect entire cylinder head area for leaks at the cup plugs.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Inspect oil filter housing for coolant leaks from oil cooler.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If no leaks are found in above areas do step 8 to inspect for upper crankcase leakage.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If coolant system pressure is dropping and no coolant is leaking from oil pan, do step
                            6.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Bar engine over by hand and check for coolant flooding the top of piston and flowing out
                    of the glow plug bore.
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>If leaks are found, do step 7.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If leaks are not found, do step 8.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cylinder head from engine following the procedures in the Engine Service Manual.
                    Perform all inspections and pressure test cylinder head to further investigate leak path. Inspect
                    cylinder head gasket for damage at sealing areas which may have caused leak. Verify crankcase and
                    cylinder head surface flatness using a straight edge and feeler gauge.
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>If glow plug or injector sleeve was replaced, retest cylinder head with pressure test
                            plate to verify repair.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove upper and lower oil pans following the procedures in the Engine Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect for leakage in crankcase.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Verify 96 kPa (14 psi) pressure is maintained on radiator pressure tester.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If no leakage is found, do step 10.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove oil cooler and oil filter housing from the engine following the procedures in the
                    Engine Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f305010408" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj13/J13038.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="592px"/>
                <caption>Air pressure leakage test</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air pressure regulator</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air adapter (make locally)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Test plate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Do oil cooler pressure test following procedures in the Engine Service Manual.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>If a leak is found, replace oil cooler assembly.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If no leak is found, do step 12.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f305010409" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="592px"/>
                <caption>Remove the front cover</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the front cover coolant sealing surfaces as follows:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Remove front cover and inspect gaskets and sealing surfaces following the procedures in
                            the Engine Service Manual.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Check front cover and crankcase following the procedures in the Engine Service Manual.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Reinstall front cover following the procedure in the Engine Service Manual.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Retest cooling system after any repair to confirm repair.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
